===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|ermine|lang=enm}}, {{term|ermin|lang=enm}}, {{term|ermyn|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|ermin|lang=fro}}, {{term|ermine|lang=fro}}, {{term|hermine|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|odt|-}} {{recons|harmino|lang=odt}} ‘stoat skin’, from {{recons|harmo|lang=odt}} ‘stoat, weasel’ (compare Dutch dialectal {{term|herm|lang=nl}}), from {{proto|Germanic|harmōn|lang=en}} (compare Old English {{term|hearma|lang=ang}}, obsolete German {{term|Harm|lang=de}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|ḱormon|lang=en}} (compare Romansch {{term|carmun|lang=rm}}, Lithuanian {{term|sarmuo|sarmuõ|lang=lt}}).

Note: The supposed derivation from {{etyl|ML.|-}} {{term|mus|mūs|lang=la}} {{term|Armenius|lang=la||Armenian mouse}} is without any foundation. <ref>{{R:Century 1911}}</ref>

